 materials. The Acknowledge action is available when the PO is in Submitted status."},{"id":"po4","text":"A PO has 3 line items. You receive items for 2 of them, but the third hasn't arrived yet. What status does the PO move to?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Received — because you recorded a receiving event"},{"id":"b","text":"Partially Received — some lines are fulfilled but not all","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Acknowledged — it stays here until everything arrives"},{"id":"d","text":"Closed — the received items are automatically closed"}],"explanation":"When some line items have been received but others still have remaining quantity, the PO moves to Partially Received. It stays in this status until all lines are fully received."},{"id":"po5","text":"When adding a line item to a PO, you select a part and the unit price auto-fills to $12.50. Where does this price come from?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The vendor's quoted price from the last PO"},{"id":"b","text":"The part's default price in the Parts Catalog","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The average of all previous purchase prices for this part"},{"id":"d","text":"A fixed system-wide default price for all parts"}],"explanation":"When you select a part on a PO line, the unit price auto-fills from the part's default price if one is set in the Parts Catalog. A tooltip indicates the price is from the part's list price. You can manually override this price."},{"id":"po6","text":"You want to cancel a PO that is in Partially Received status. Is this possible?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Yes — any PO can be cancelled at any time"},{"id":"b","text":"No — only Draft, Submitted, and Acknowledged POs can be cancelled","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Yes — but only if you return the received items first"},{"id":"d","text":"No — you must close it instead of cancelling"}],"explanation":"The Cancel action is only available for POs in Draft, Submitted, or Acknowledged status. Once items have been received (Partially Received or Received), the PO cannot be cancelled — it must proceed through the receiving workflow to Closed."},{"id":"po7","text":"In the Receive Items dialog, what does the 'Receive All' button do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Marks the entire PO as Received regardless of actual quantities"},{"id":"b","text":"Fills in the remaining quantity for every receivable line item","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Creates a new receiving record with zero quantities for audit purposes"},{"id":"d","text":"Closes the PO and archives all line items"}],"explanation":"Receive All is a convenience button that fills in the remaining quantity for every line that still has outstanding items. This is useful when a complete shipment arrives and you don't need to enter quantities line by line. You still need to click Save to record the receipt."},{"id":"po8","text":"What is a blanket purchase order?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"A PO that covers all parts from a single vendor at once"},{"id":"b","text":"A long-term agreement for a total quantity at an agreed price, with individual releases over time","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"A PO template that auto-generates new POs on a schedule"},{"id":"d","text":"A PO that has been approved by management for large expenditures"}],"explanation":"A blanket PO is a long-term purchasing agreement with a vendor. You commit to a total quantity at an agreed unit price, then create individual releases over time as you need materials delivered. Each release specifies a quantity and requested delivery date."},{"id":"po9","text":"A PO line item shows Ordered: 100, Received: 75, Remaining: 25. What does this tell you?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The vendor has shipped all 100 units but 25 were rejected during inspection"},{"id":"b","text":"75 units have arrived and been recorded; 25 units are still outstanding","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"You originally ordered 75 but increased the order to 100"},{"id":"d","text":"25 units are on backorder and the rest were cancelled"}],"explanation":"Remaining Quantity is calculated as Ordered minus Received. Here, 75 units have been physically received and recorded through the Receive Items workflow. 25 units are still expected from the vendor."},{"id":"po10","text":"You need to delete a purchase order. Under what condition is this allowed?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Any PO can be deleted at any time by an admin"},{"id":"b","text":"Only POs in Draft status can be deleted","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"POs can be deleted only after they are Cancelled"},{"id":"d","text":"POs are never deleted — they can only be archived"}],"explanation":"The Delete action is only available for Draft POs. Once a PO has been submitted or progressed further in the lifecycle, it cannot be deleted — it can only be cancelled (if eligible) or closed. Delete requires a confirmation dialog with danger severity."},{"id":"po11","text":"You want to see all POs from a specific vendor that are waiting for materials. Which filters do you apply?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Set the Vendor filter to the vendor name and Status filter to Acknowledged or Partially Received","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Search for the vendor name in the search box — no other filters needed"},{"id":"c","text":"Set the Status filter to Submitted and sort by vendor name"},{"id":"d","text":"Go to the vendor's detail page and look at the PO tab"}],"explanation":"Use the Vendor dropdown to select the specific vendor, then set the Status filter. POs that are 'waiting for materials' are in Acknowledged status (vendor confirmed, awaiting shipment) or Partially Received (some items arrived, still waiting for more)."},{"id":"po12","text":"After all items on a PO are received, what is the next step to finalize the order?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Delete the PO to clear it from the list"},{"id":"b","text":"Click Close PO to formally close the order","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The PO automatically