            ContentJson = """{"title":"Closing a PO Short","groups":[{"heading":"What Short-Close Means","items":[{"label":"What it is","value":"Short-closing finishes off a partly-received order when the rest will never arrive — and you're OK with that. It closes the order with a reason on record instead of waiting for a balance that isn't coming."},{"label":"Normal Close vs. Short-Close","value":"The regular Close only works once an order is fully received — it won't close one that still has items outstanding. Short-Close is how you close an order that's only partly received."},{"label":"Typical reasons","value":"The vendor cancelled the backorder, the item was discontinued, you no longer need the rest, or the small balance left isn't worth chasing."}]},{"heading":"When the Button Appears","items":[{"label":"Status","value":"Short Close shows on any order that isn't Draft, Closed, or Cancelled — in practice, Submitted, Acknowledged, or Partially Received orders that still have items outstanding."},{"label":"Something must be outstanding","value":"At least one line must still have items to come. If everything's already received, use the normal Close instead."},{"label":"Who can do it","value":"Available to Admins, Managers, Office Managers, and Purchasing. Others won't see the Short Close button."}]},{"heading":"How to Short-Close","items":[{"label":"1. Open the PO","value":"Click the order's row on the Orders tab to open it."},{"label":"2. Click Short Close","value":"Find Short Close alongside the Cancel and Close actions."},{"label":"3. Enter a reason","value":"A window opens and asks for a reason. It's required — you can't confirm until you enter one."},{"label":"4. Confirm","value":"Click Short Close to confirm. The order moves to Closed and the leftover quantities are marked as short-closed."}]},{"heading":"What Gets Recorded","items":[{"label":"Short-Closed Quantity","value":"Whatever wasn't received on each line is recorded as short-closed. Afterward, the lines show an extra column with these amounts."},{"label":"Reason and date","value":"The order shows a 'Short Closed' note with the reason you gave and the date, so accounts payable and purchasing can see at a glance why it closed with items unfilled."},{"label":"Final status","value":"The order ends up Closed. Nothing more can be received, cancelled, or changed — short-close is final, just like a normal close."}]},{"heading":"Short-Close vs. Cancel","items":[{"label":"Cancel","value":"Only for Draft, Submitted, and Acknowledged orders — before anything has arrived. It voids the whole order."},{"label":"Short-Close","value":"Used after some items have arrived. It keeps what you received (and its records) and only closes out the part that didn't come."},{"label":"Rule of thumb","value":"Nothing received and the whole order is off → Cancel. Some received, the rest won't come → Short-Close."}]}]}"""
